                    },
                    "body": "Why does the order matter, exactly? These are key\/value pairs, and order should not be an issue. Can you explain the use case?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-19T06:40:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-19T06:40:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43149",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=2called-chaos",
                        "name": "2called-chaos",
                        "displayName": "2called-chaos",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In my case it is a bit of aesthetics and sense...\r\n{quote}\r\n\/payment\/select\/pay-method\/for-product\/foo\/with-addons\/bar,baz\r\n{quote}\r\nmakes more sense and looks better than\r\n{quote}\r\n\/payment\/select\/pay-method\/with-addons\/bar,baz\/for-product\/foo\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nJust my opinion but I think it's intuitive or expected that new things will be appended instead of be placed anywhere in the middle...\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\nChaos",
